qryXMLSLATIDetail.Description:
Cigars: 65% of the wholesale sales price of cigars, but not to exceed 50 cents per cigar;
Moist snuff: $1.78/oz. except the minimum tax is $2.14 per retail container;
All other tobacco products: 65% of the wholesale sales price.
OR. REV. STAT. § 323.505 (2014).

Note: For tax reporting periods beginning on or after July 1, 2022, the rates of tax applicable to moist snuff shall be adjusted for each biennium according to a cost-of-living adjustment for the calendar year as specified.
